### SPECIAL DRAWING RIGHTS ###
categories {
  title: "Special Drawing Rights"
  description: "Special Drawing Rights (SDRs) are an important financing source for African countries to respond to ongoing and future crises. SDRs, which are created by the IMF, provide a much needed injection of liquidity to plug fiscal gaps, meet external debt obligations, or address foreign exchange shortages.They are allocated according to a country’s relative size in the global economy — so richer countries receive the lion’s share. The most recent SDR allocation equivalent to $650 billion took place in August 2021 to help countries respond to the COVID-19 pandemic."

